urlLink Instructional Models for Early Childhood Education. ERIC Digest.   This ERIC Digest is written by Susan Golbeck.  It examines different instructional models that are often used when teaching little kids.  From the ERIC Digest:  What is the best approach for teaching young children? No question could be more pressing as teachers, researchers, and policy makers strive to make sure all children are "ready to learn." Yet, as of now, there is no definitive answer. This Digest discusses the existing knowledge base on the differential effects of various approaches to early education. Concurrently, the field eagerly anticipates results from the recently funded Preschool Curriculum Evaluation Research initiative, which will use randomized trials to examine a variety of preschool curricular approaches.